<div id="wikicontent"><div class="page"><h3 id="s1_1">Mushrooms</h3><p>This list is ordered by depth, then by cost, then alphabetically<table border="1"><tr><td>Name</td><td>Description</td><td>Cost</td><td>Depth</td><td>Rarity</td><td>Damage</td></tr><tr><td>Blindness</td><td>Causes blindness that lasts for 199+1d200 turns, unless your character has resistance to blindness</td><td>0</td><td>5</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Confusion</td><td>Causes confusion that lasts for 9+1d10 turns, unless your character has resistance to confusion</td><td>0</td><td>5</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Paranoia</td><td>Causes fear that lasts for 9+1d10 turns, unless your character has resistance to fear</td><td>0</td><td>5</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Poison</td><td>Poisons your character for 9+1d10 turns, unless he or she has resistance to poison</td><td>0</td><td>5</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Hallucination</td><td>Causes your character to hallucinate for 249+1d250 turns, unless he or she has resistance to chaos</td><td>0</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Sickness</td><td>Inflicts some damage, and also reduces constitution by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain constitution</td><td>0</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td>6d6</td></tr><tr><td>Weakness</td><td>Inflicts some damage, and also reduces strength by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain strength</td><td>0</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td>6d6</td></tr><tr><td>Cure Paranoia</td><td>Cures fear</td><td>25</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Cure Blindness</td><td>Cures blindness</td><td>50</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Cure Confusion</td><td>Cures confusion</td><td>50</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Cure Poison</td><td>Neutralizes poison</td><td>60</td><td>10</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Naivety</td><td>Inflicts some damage, and also reduces wisdom by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain wisdom</td><td>0</td><td>15</td><td>1</td><td>8d8</td></tr><tr><td>Stupidity</td><td>Inflicts some damage, and also reduces intelligence by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain intelligence</td><td>0</td><td>15</td><td>1</td><td>8d8</td></tr><tr><td>Unhealth</td><td>Inflicts considerable damage, and also reduces constitution by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain constitution; it may also be thrown to inflict the same level of damage</td><td>50</td><td>15</td><td>1</td><td>10d10</td></tr><tr><td>Cure Serious Wounds</td><td>Cures 4d8 points of damage</td><td>75</td><td>15</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Paralysis</td><td>Causes paralysis that lasts for 9+1d10 turns, unless your character has free action</td><td>0</td><td>20</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Disease</td><td>Inflicts considerable damage, and also reduces strength by 2.5 to 5%, unless your character has sustain strength; it may also be thrown to inflict the same level of damage</td><td>50</td><td>20</td><td>1</td><td>10d10</td></tr><tr><td>Restore Constitution</td><td>Restores constitution to maximum</td><td>350</td><td>20</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Restore Strength</td><td>Restores strength to maximum</td><td>350</td><td>20</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Restoring</td><td>Restores all stats to maximum</td><td>1,000</td><td>20</td><td>8</td><td></td></tr></table><p>Notes<ul><li>Mushrooms weigh 0.1lbs<li>Unless otherwise indicated, mushrooms inflict no damage when thrown<li>Mushrooms cannot be harmed by acid, cold, fire or lightning<li>Mushrooms provide nourishment for about 500 turns under normal conditions<li>Timed effects are cumulative with similar effects already in action</ul></div></div>

